<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-20524] Fix race in CollectionVirtualTableAdapter</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-20524</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;buildDataRangeIterator&lt;/tt&gt; in &lt;tt&gt;CollectionVirtualTableAdapter&lt;/tt&gt; uses parallel streams, this requires the inner map in &lt;tt&gt;partitionMap&lt;/tt&gt; to be concurrent, otherwise we could lose rows. This reproduces in &lt;tt&gt;CollectionVirtualTableAdapterTest&lt;/tt&gt; when run on JDK21 where several threads are actually used when calling &lt;tt&gt;StreamSupport.stream(..., true)&lt;/tt&gt;. It also reproduces in real scenarios on JDK11 when there are more entries in &lt;tt&gt;data.spliterator()&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I doubt we gain much by having this use parallel streams, we should rewrite it to be a simple for loop.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
